  "prompt": "What are some side dishes for tortellini?",
  "response": "Tortellini is a versatile pasta that pairs well with a variety of side dishes. Here are some great options to complement your meal:\n\n### **Vegetable Sides**\n1. **Garlic Saut\u00e9ed Spinach**: Quick, healthy, and adds a pop of green.\n2. **Roasted Vegetables**: Think zucchini, bell peppers, cherry tomatoes, and asparagus.\n3. **Caprese Salad**: Fresh mozzarella, tomatoes, basil, and balsamic glaze.\n4. **Steamed Broccoli**: Simple and nutritious.\n5. **Grilled or Roasted Asparagus**: Light and flavorful.\n6. **Green Beans Almondine**: Green beans with toasted almonds and butter.\n\n### **Salad Options**\n1. **Arugula Salad**: With shaved Parmesan, lemon juice, and olive oil.\n2. **Caesar Salad**: Classic and creamy.\n3. **Antipasto Salad**: A mix of olives, artichokes, roasted peppers, and cheeses.\n4. **Tomato Cucumber Salad**: Fresh and refreshing with a light vinaigrette.\n\n### **Bread Sides**\n1. **Garlic Bread**: Warm and buttery, perfect for mopping up sauces.\n2. **Focaccia**: Soft, herby, and great for dipping.\n3. **Bruschetta**: Toasted bread topped with tomatoes, basil, and olive oil.\n\n### **Other Complementary Sides**\n1. **Soup**: Pair with a light soup like minestrone or tomato basil.\n2. **Grilled Chicken or Shrimp**: For added protein.\n3. **Stuffed Mushrooms**: A savory and hearty option.\n4. **Cheese Board**: Served with cured meats, olives, and nuts.\n\n### **Light and Fresh Options**\n1. **Seasonal Fruit Salad**: A sweet and refreshing contrast.\n2. **Marinated Artichoke Hearts**: Tangy and flavorful.\n\nThese side dishes can enhance your tortellini meal, whether you\u2019re serving it with a creamy sauce, tomato-based sauce, or simply tossed in olive oil and herbs.",
